<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-008-123 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 588 841</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Nov 25 1991 v13 n47 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Claris moves to put troubles behind; revamps support, developerplan.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Picarille, Lisa.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Claris Corp hopes for better times ahead as it recovers from atumultuous 1991, during which the company experienced a 100percent management turnover, an aborted public offering,technology agreements that fell through, and a spinoff from Appleand a subsequent buyback.andP;  The company is developing aworkgroup-oriented system that should account for 30 to 40 percentof Claris's revenues by the mid-1990s, according to Claris Presand CEO Dan Eilers.andP;  The workgroup system is conceived as atask-oriented product that will allow users to change theirdesktops according to the task they want to accomplish.andP;  Claris isalso revamping its support program so that users can select fromseveral levels of service support.andP;  The company is inaugurating aprogram that will aggressively pursue licensing deals andacquisitions with small developers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Claris Corp. (Planning).andO;Topic:     ReorganizationRevenueSupport ServicesVendor RelationsMismanagementCustomer Relations.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>